OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Sat 25 Apr to Mon 4 May
OL,6,FHigh pressure is likely to be centred
OL,7,Fclose to or across the UK through much
OL,8,Fof this period, so many places will be
OL,9,Flargely dry with clear or sunny
OL,10,Fperiods. Some showery rain may affect
OL,11,Fnorthern and western parts this
OL,12,Fweekend though. Colder air will also
OL,13,Ftry to push into the country from the
OL,14,Fnorth this weekend but will probably
OL,15,Fonly briefly make limited progress
OL,16,Finto the northeast, where it could
OL,17,Fbring a short-lived showery interlude,
OL,18,Fsome of these wintry. Winds will be
OL,19,Fmostly light, but briefly stronger in
OL,20,Fthe northeast as the colder air tries
OL,21,Fto come south. Temperatures will
OL,22,Fprobably be near or slightly above
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fnormal for many, but with a risk of
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,Fcolder conditions affecting the north
OL,25,For more especially the northeast this
OL,26,Fweekend.
